# EJS Views & Bootstrap Rules

## Layout Parts
Shared partials live in `views/parts/` — always include them in this order:
1. `head.ejs` → `head-end.ejs`
2. `body.ejs` (renders `navigation.ejs` inside)
3. Page content inside `<main>`
4. `body-end.ejs`

## Partials Catalogue
- `navigation.ejs` — desktop + mobile nav; renders signed-in username badge via `res.locals.userName`; includes `success-notification.ejs` at the bottom.
- `success-notification.ejs` — Bootstrap dismissible alert, shows when `locals.successMessage` is set.
- `error-msg.ejs` — shows flash error (`res.locals.error`).
- `add-to-cart.ejs` — reusable add-to-cart form posting hidden `id` to `POST /cart`.

## Bootstrap Usage
- Use Bootstrap CDN (already included in `head.ejs`) — do not add a local copy.
- Cards for product listings, `list-group` for cart/order items, `badge text-bg-secondary` for user name in nav.
- Use `btn btn-primary` / `btn btn-danger` for actions consistently.
- Use `alert alert-success alert-dismissible fade show` for success notifications.

## Forms
- Reuse `views/parts/add-to-cart.ejs` for add-to-cart actions — do not duplicate inline.
- Hidden `<input name="id">` carries product id to `POST /cart`.
- All forms use `method="POST"`; no client-side fetch unless explicitly requested.
- Every POST form **must** include `<input type="hidden" name="_csrf" value="<%= csrfToken %>">`.

## Variable Contract
Every rendered view receives at minimum via `res.locals`:
- `pageTitle` — used in `<title>` tag inside `head.ejs`
- `url` — active nav link indicator in `navigation.ejs`
- `isLoggedIn` — controls nav item visibility
- `csrfToken` — required on all POST forms
- `error` — flash error array (set via `req.flash('error', ...)`)
- `success` — flash success array (set via `req.flash('success', ...)`)
- `userName` — signed-in user display name (empty string when not logged in)

## Auth Views Location
Auth-related EJS files live in `views/auth/`:
- `login.ejs`, `signup.ejs`, `reset.ejs`, `reset-password.ejs`

## Do Not
- Do not add inline `<style>` blocks; use `public/css/*.css` instead.
- Do not introduce a JS framework (React, Vue) — views are server-rendered EJS only.
- Do not duplicate `_csrf` hidden field logic; always reference `csrfToken` local.

